Independent analyst Chris Gilmour chose Afrimat as his stock pick of the day and Drikus Combrinck from Capicraft chose Alliance Resource Partners. Gilmour said: “I’m going to revert to one of my old favourites — Afrimat. Their results came out on Monday. Iron ore is currently trading into the high hundreds [of dollars] and into the early $200s now.” Combrinck said: “I’m going with a with a coal producer, the second biggest in the US, it’s called Alliance Resource Partners  and they come up with first-quarter results if you just extrapolate the first quarter, which was horrendous then they’re sitting at a 12% dividend yield.” Or listen to the full audio: Subscribe for free episodes: iono.fm | Spotify | Pocket Casts | Player.fm